    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_jm.00254.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <date when="1890-08-07">Aug&#8212;7<hi rend="underline">th</hi> 1890.</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Walt Whitman</salute>  
            </opener>
            <p>The ever recurring thought comes, to me to ask you for your Autograph,
                and now I do. This is the first time in a life of sixty years, that I have
                ever made such a request of anyone.</p>
            <p>I have two of your books, Leaves of Grass, and Two Rivulets<ptr target="loc.08229_n3"/>; they have
                been a light to my steps, these many years.
            </p>
            <closer> 
                <salute>Yours most truly,</salute>
                <signed>Julia A. J. Perkins.</signed>
                <address>
                    <addrLine>Baldwinsville</addrLine>
                    <addrLine>Onondaga Co. N.Y.</addrLine>
                </address> 
                <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc_jm.00255.jpg" type="verso"/>
            </closer>
        </body>
    </text>
